import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    missing_values = data['rate'].isnull().sum()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(['Missing Values'], [missing_values], color='red')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('Are there any missing values in the rate field of the dataset?')
    ax.axhline(y=missing_values, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Missing Values: {missing_values:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['rate'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, 
               labels=['Rate'])
    ax.set_title('What is the range of rate values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {data["rate"].min():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {data["rate"].max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
